    "F: Y -> X and G: X -> Y to classify an input picture as genuine or fake.",
    "Figure 11 shows the translation of horse images into Zebra images using Cycle GAN.In the course of training, two distinct types of training observations are provided as input.1.",
    "One group of observations has paired pictures labelled \"Xi, Yi,\" where each Xi is accompanied by its corresponding Yi. 2.",
    "The additional set of observations consists of two different sets of photographs: one class of images from X and another class of images of Y, but there is no match between the two sets.",
    "The generators include an encoder, a convolutional network that decreases an image's size, and a decoder, a transpose-convolutional network that alters the image.Using cross-entropy loss, the discriminator determines whether a picture is false or genuine."
